originalText.text:
While wandering around the Upper East Side, I stumbled upon Ikyu 一休, a sushi restaurant that immediately caught my attention. This spotless and aesthetically pleasing establishment offers an impressive variety of sushi and Asian Fusion Cuisine.

From the moment I stepped in, I was captivated by the restaurant's inviting atmosphere. The array of sushi options available was both extensive and intriguing, catering to a wide range of tastes and preferences. Each dish I tried was a testament to the excellent ingredients' quality. The sushi was fresh, expertly prepared, and presented beautifully, making each bite a delightful experience.

Ikyu 一休 is a real find for anyone in the Upper East Side looking for high-quality sushi in an attractive setting. Whether you're a sushi connoisseur or just exploring the delights of Asian Fusion Cuisine, this restaurant is definitely worth a visit.

originalText.text: Great new sushi place in the area. We were able to walk in on Sunday night and eat at the sushi bar (there were tables too). Service was super fast & staff was very nice. Prices are reasonable but some of the portions were small (crispy rice with tuna & the rock shrimp were smaller than we expected). Otherwise, food was good! Will definitely come back here and try more rolls. Front of the restaurant is a little bright for my liking but the back had better lighting & atmosphere.

originalText.text: 9/10!! Ikyu had amazing staff. My girlfriend accidentally dropped a chopstick, and they immediately came to give a new one. Sometimes, it’s the little things. The sushi rolls were slightly expensive anywhere from $10-20. The plate in front of me is the Salmon Fizz Roll and a Shrimp Tempura Roll behind it. The one on the other plate was a Salmon Skin roll. All of them were served well. The fish was fresh, the ingredients were prepped properly, and overall was a very enjoyable experience. For desert, we tried the cream cheese ice cream with honey and peanuts (I know sounds weird). The server even made shredded to ask if we were allergic to peanuts which some servers don’t do enough honestly. After a while it did grow on me, and it felt like the dish only came together when you had all three on a spoon. The honey with only the ice cream felt misplaced. So I’d give desert a 6.5/10. The ambiance is really nice, and definitely makes for a great spot to eat whether you’re on a date or by yourself (They have stools in front of the sushi bar). Definitely would go again!

originalText.text:
Our experience here was just wonderful. You start with a really nice and simple decor. The music is quite and relaxing.

We tried scallion pancake and miso soup for starters and then got some rolls. Even the dishes are pretty there. Did I mention that for 3$ they bring you not just a cup but a big pot of green tea?

Highly recommend this place

originalText.text:
Food: There are a lot of options when it comes to food and drinks. There are so many veggie rolls to pick from and they even made something off menu for my husband. I got the veggie tempura roll and it was so yummy. They actually had all types of veggies in it and it was perfectly crispy. We got 2 appetizers there - the veggie gyoza and the scallion pancake. The scallion pancakes were delicious and perfectly flavored. I will say that the veggie gyoza tasted like all others I've had at other restaurants, good but not excellent. There are a few other veggie apps I definitely plan to try when we go back. My husband got an off menu avocado peanut roll. This is one of the few sushi places where I felt like they didn't skimp  on the avocado or peanuts. The drinks menu looked delicious but we weren't really feeling like alcohol so we got a pot of tea. The tea comes in this beautiful pot with very nice cups. We're big tea drinkers and are pretty specific about our teas and their jasmine tea was very nice - beautiful blend of different flavors.  This whole pot of premium jasmine tea was $3!? We were stunned!

Service: The staff is very friendly and the service is very fast even when they are really busy.

Ambiance: This place is so cute. I love the theme, it feels very modern but comfortable at the same time. It's great spot for dates or small groups. All their dishware and glassware was so beautiful and perfectly in theme with the restaurant.

Price: The prices are very reasonable and I was very surprised at the amount of food we were able to get for less than $40 for 2 people. We got 2 appetizers, 2 sushi rolls, and a big pot of tea. Bonus: Unlike most places, they didn't charge us extra for sriracha or spicy mayo.

Overall, this was such an amazing dining experience. I am so grateful it's in our local neighborhood so we can keep coming back. Our favorite sushi place closed down post COVID so we are ecstatic to have found Ikyu.

If you found this review helpful, please let me know :)

Also, add me on Instagram: @TheShahLALand
